Commentary Text: Khaleel Ahmed to Mujeeb, out Caught by Bairstow!! An appeal for caught-behind, SRH decide against the review. Meanwhile, the umpires have sent it upstairs to check if it was a bump ball. The soft signal is Not Out. A yorker length ball from round the wicket, Mujeeb stays leg-side of the ball to jam it out. Don't think it is a bump ball. OUT signalled on the giant screen. And, the drama doesn't end there. Mujeeb starts to walk ... and then decides to challenge the call. The umpires had a chat and decided to call the third umpire, again! A review for caught-behind. There's a spike on Ultra Edge and it's clearly an outside edge as the bat hits the ground later. After all the drama, Mujeeb is out and he's wasted a review too. Mujeeb c Bairstow b Khaleel Ahmed 1(3)

Commentary Text: Khaleel Ahmed to Rahul, 1 run, a direct-hit at the keeper's end could have had the new batsman in trouble. Rahul had flicked the inswinger towards mid-wicket from where the throw came in. Bairstow did well to collect it and take off the bails, but a direct-hit was the need of the hour for Hyderabad. Well, as I look at the replays it could probably have been a direct-hit had Jonny not collected the ball in front of the stumps

Commentary Text: Khaleel Ahmed to Agarwal, out Agarwal Run Out!! 1 run completed. A mix-up between the openers and Mayank has to depart. Brilliant stop by Warner at mid-off though. He sprinted across and stopped the drive with a dive. Mayank was committed for the second, but Rahul sends him back. And by the time he can react, Warner's throw is already at the bowler's end. That's that for Agarwal tonight, then. Agarwal run out (Warner/Khaleel Ahmed) 9(6) [4s-1]
